Transcription.Text: The man had obviously fallen down on his job. In some way, every occupant of the penthouse had left the premises - and Landis had not seen them go. It was understandable that Aunt Susan and Livingstone had escaped the watcher's attention; but it was incredible that he could have missed such figures as those of Norman and Joy.
